{
  "question_id": "1bd815b7-e5ed-4982-9222-1f2cbdc59b4f",
  "short_text": "Hollow Right Angled Triangle - 2",
  "content": "Given a number `N`, write a program to print a **Right Angled Triangle** of `N` rows using underscore (`_`), pipe (`|`), and forward slash (`/`).\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n#### Input\r\n\r\nThe input will be a single line containing an integer representing `N`.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n#### Output\r\n\r\nThe output should be `N` rows containing underscore (`_`), pipe (`|`), and forward slash (`/`) as a **Right Angled Triangle** shown in the sample output. \r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n#### Explanation\r\n\r\nFor example, if the given number is `N = 5`,\r\n\r\n- Print underscore (`_`), pipes (`|`), and forward slashes (`/`) on **6** rows as shown in the given image.\r\n  - The first row contains **6** underscores.\r\n  - The next **5** rows contain pipe (`|`) and forward slash (`/`).\r\n\r\n<Img imageSrc='https://assets.ccbp.in/frontend/content/programming-foundations/cx-hollow-right-angled-triangle-2-v2.png' widthPercent='60'/>\r\n\r\n<MultiLineNote>\r\nIn the given image,\r\n\r\n- The Empty box indicates a space (\" \").\r\n- The Underscore in the box indicates an underscore (\"_\").\r\n- The Pipe in the box indicates a pipe (\"|\").\r\n- The Forward slash in the box indicates a forward slash (\"/\").\r\n</MultiLineNote>\r\n\r\n\r\n```\r\n______\r\n|    /\r\n|   /\r\n|  /\r\n| /\r\n|/\r\n```",
  "question_type": "CODING",
  "content_type": "MARKDOWN",
  "codes": [
    {
      "code_id": "d2886cdc-0222-4abe-8711-09e63e4caaa9",
      "code_content": "n = int(input())\n\nprint(\"_\" * (n + 1))\nfor i in range(n):\n    print(\"|\" + \" \" * (n - 1 - i) + \"/\")",
      "language": "PYTHON",
      "default_code": true
    }
